Plugin: Don't register SIGSEGV and SIGILL handlers

The plugin has fault handlers which catch faults and continue.  This
is risky: it is likely to hide bugs in the code during development.
It is also not fail-safe.

Leave the SIGPIPE handler in for now.  It would require different
testing to remove.

BUG=http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=605
TEST=existing tests

